.TH "ib_umem_odp_get" 9 "ib_umem_odp_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_umem_odp_get \- Create a umem_odp for a userspace va
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_umem_odp *" ib_umem_odp_get
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int access "  ","
.BI "const struct mmu_interval_notifier_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
IB device struct to get UMEM
.IP "addr" 12
userspace virtual address to start at
.IP "size" 12
length of region to pin
.IP "access" 12
IB_ACCESS_xxx flags for memory being pinned
.IP "ops" 12
MMU interval ops, currently only \fIinvalidate\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The driver should use when the access flags indicate ODP memory. It avoids
pinning, instead, stores the mm for future page fault handling in
conjunction with MMU notifiers.
